The paper deals with algorithms for computing the discrete Fr\'echet distance, which is a well-studied problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also uses techniques from data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM) to develop faster algorithms for the problem. Additionally, the paper discusses applications of the discrete Fr\'echet distance in similarity search and approximation algorithms, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational complexity (cs.SI).
